\begin_inset Formula $F_{m}\leq k+1<F_{m+1}$
\end_inset

.
 This allows us to write
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
k+1 & =F_{m}+\left(k+1-F_{m}\right).
\end{align*}

\end_inset

 We have two cases to consider.
 When 
\begin_inset Formula $k+1-F_{m}=0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $k+1-F_{m}>0$
\end_inset

.
